A vintage-style illustration of a detective with a magnifying glass peering beneath the surface of an old wooden desk, revealing a hidden compartment filled with glowing red filing cards and mysterious documents. The scene is rendered in warm sepia tones with aged paper textures, showing dust motes floating in amber lamplight. The desk's surface appears semi-transparent like a cross-section diagram from a 1950s technical manual, exposing intricate hidden mechanisms and secret drawers underneath. Small brass gears and clockwork elements suggest the complexity hidden from plain view. The detective wears period-appropriate attire with rolled sleeves, intensely focused on uncovering what lies beneath the ordinary surface.
